The paper discusses Adversarial Machine Learning (AML) and its protection against security threats. The primary focus is on game-theoretic approaches to AML, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). However, the paper also discusses Bayesian Adversarial Risk Analysis, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and system security (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of AML in computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, and cs.CV.
